@page
<!-- This is the Razor Page for the "Privacy Policy" page of "The Books" website. -->

<!-- The page directive indicates that this file represents a Razor Page. -->


<!-- Set the model for this Razor Page to be the PrivacyModel. -->
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    // Set the page title dynamically using ViewData["Title"].
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<!-- Display the page title in an h1 heading. -->
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<!-- Introduce the privacy policy and its purpose with a paragraph. -->
<p>
    At The Books, we are committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and safeguard your personal information when you visit our website.
</p>

<!-- Section: Information We Collect -->
<h2>Information We Collect</h2>
<p>
    We may collect the following types of information when you visit our website:
</p>
<ul>
    <!-- List item: Collecting name and email address for newsletter subscription. -->
    <li>Your name and email address when you subscribe to our newsletter.</li>
    <!-- List item: Collecting non-personal information for analytical purposes. -->
    <li>Non-personal information, such as your IP address and browser type, for analytical purposes.</li>
</ul>

<!-- Section: How We Use Your Information -->
<h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
<p>
    The information we collect may be used for the following purposes:
</p>
<ul>
    <!-- List item: Sending newsletters and updates if subscribed to the newsletter. -->
    <li>To send you newsletters and updates about our latest book releases and promotions, if you have subscribed to our newsletter.</li>
    <!-- List item: Analyzing website traffic for performance and user experience improvement. -->
    <li>To analyze website traffic and improve our website's performance and user experience.</li>
</ul>

<!-- Section: Third-Party Services -->
<h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
<p>
    We may use third-party services, such as Google Analytics, to track and analyze website traffic. These services may collect non-personal information about your interactions with our website.
</p>

<!-- Section: Cookies -->
<h2>Cookies</h2>
<p>
    We may use cookies to enhance your browsing experience. Cookies are small text files stored on your device when you visit our website. You can adjust your browser settings to disable cookies if you prefer not to receive them.
</p>

<!-- Section: Data Security -->
<h2>Data Security</h2>
<p>
    We take data security seriously and implement appropriate measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, alteration, or disclosure.
</p>

<!-- Section: Changes to this Privacy Policy -->
<h2>Changes to this Privacy Policy</h2>
<p>
    We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or for other operational, legal, or regulatory reasons. The updated Privacy Policy will be posted on this page, and the changes will be effective upon posting.
</p>

<!-- Contact Information -->
<p>
    If you have any questions or concerns regarding our Privacy Policy, please contact us at privacy@thebooks.com.
</p>
